Title: JOSEPHINE COTTON, as guardian of the minor Genevieve Cynthia Baltao,petitioner,vs.HON. NATIVIDAD ALMEDA-LOPEZ, as Judge of the Juvenile & Domestic Relations Court of the City of Manila, and EUGENIO S. BALTAO,respondents.
Data:
Republic of the Philippines
SUPREME COURT
Manila


EN BANC 


G.R. No. L-14113           November 21, 1961


JOSEPHINE COTTON, as guardian of the minor Genevieve Cynthia Baltao,
 petitioner,

vs.


HON. NATIVIDAD ALMEDA-LOPEZ, as Judge of the Juvenile & Domestic Relations Court of the City of Manila, and EUGENIO S. BALTAO,
 respondents.


Lino M. Patajo and Eugenio T. Estavillo for respondents.

Jose W. Diokno for petitioner.


R E S O L U T I O N


LABRADOR, 
J.:


Upon considering the motion for reconsideration filed by petitioner and it appearing that the obligations imposed upon respondent Eugenio S. Baltao by the judgment were complied with by said Baltao only after a court order, the motion to reconsider the grant of costs against petitioner is hereby granted and the decision is, with respect to the grant of costs to respondent Baltao, set aside.


Bengzon, C.J., Padilla, Bautista Angelo, Concepcion, Reyes, J.B.L., Barrera, Paredes, Dizon and De Leon, JJ.,
 concur.
